				<h2>BSD, C, httpd, SQLite.</h2>
				<p itemprop="description">
					BCHS (pronounced /biːtʃəz/, <i>beaches</i>) is for real development.
					It's a hipster-free, <a href="https://www.openbsd.org/policy.html">open source</a> software stack for web
					applications.
					To prepare a BCHS environment, install <a href="https://www.openbsd.org">OpenBSD</a>.
					Then <a href="start.html">get started</a>.
				</p>
				<p>
					Don't care for talk?
					<a href="easy.html">See an easy example</a>.
					For more, see
					<a href="https://kristaps.bsd.lv/absdcon2016/">Secure CGI Applications in C on BSD</a> 
					(or its <a href="https://kristaps.bsd.lv//absdcon2017">follow-up</a>);
					<a href="pledge.html">BCHS sandboxing</a>;
					using <a href="json.html">JSON</a> with BCHS; or for something completely new,
					<a href="kwebapp.html">kwebapp</a>.
				</p>
				<p>
					Is BCHS a joke?
					No.  
					Software development is full of jokes.
					This is not one of them.
				</p>
